- You want to make the nested list using Google Docs API.
- As a test case, you want to achieve as follows. The following image is from [here](https://developers.google.com/docs/api/how-tos/lists#convert_a_paragraph_to_a_list).

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

If my understanding is correct, how about this answer?

## Solution:
When [the document](https://developers.google.com/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/documents/request#createparagraphbulletsrequest) is confirmed, the following document can be seen.

&gt; The nesting level of each paragraph will be determined by counting leading tabs in front of each paragraph. To avoid excess space between the bullet and the corresponding paragraph, these leading tabs are removed by this request. This may change the indices of parts of the text.

From this, when you want to create the nested list, please use `\t` at the top of paragraph. For example, when the following paragraphs are put to the Document,

	Item One
	Item Two
		Sub-Item One
		Sub-Item Two
	Item Three

it becomes as follows.

	Item One\nItem Two\n\tSub-Item One\n\tSub-Item Two\nItem Three\n

Using this, the endpoint and request body are as follows.

### Endpoint:
	POST https://docs.googleapis.com/v1/documents/{documentId}:batchUpdate

### Sample request body:
For the situation the paragraphs are existing, please use `createParagraphBullets`.

	{
	  &quot;requests&quot;: 
	  [
	    {
	      &quot;insertText&quot;: 
	      {
	        &quot;location&quot;: 
	        {
	          &quot;index&quot;: 1
	        },
	        &quot;text&quot;: &quot;Item One\nItem Two\n\tSub-Item One\n\tSub-Item Two\nItem Three\n&quot;
	      }
	    },
	    {
	      &quot;createParagraphBullets&quot;: 
	      {
	        &quot;range&quot;: 
	        {
	          &quot;startIndex&quot;: 1,
	          &quot;endIndex&quot;: 50
	        },
	        &quot;bulletPreset&quot;: &quot;BULLET_ARROW_DIAMOND_DISC&quot;
	      }
	    }
	  ]
	}

- For example, if the paragraphs have already been existing in the Document, you can only use `createParagraphBullets`.
- It seems that about `endIndex` of `createParagraphBullets`, when the paragraph is included, the request works for the paragraph.

By above endpoint and request body, the nested list can be created.

### Reference:
- [CreateParagraphBulletsRequest](https://developers.google.com/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/documents/request#createparagraphbulletsrequest)

If I misunderstood your question and this was not the direction you want, I apologize.


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/GYuts.png

